### Key Learnings
1. 1 scout is optimal. 2 scouts has higher variance, 3 scouts = diminishing returns.
2. Dense spiral pattern is WORSE than wide pattern — spacing matters.
3. Scouts should ONLY scout. Multitasking (align, scramble) hurts exploration.
4. Scout phase transition (explore→aligner) is terrible. Permanent scouting best.
5. Both Cogs sub-teams share team_id='cogs' → scramble already only hits Clips.

